  "text": "Childhood obesity is associated with an increased risk for several metabolic complications, such as insulin resistance, glucose intolerance and type 2 diabetes mellitus (T2DM). In particular, insulin resistance is the most common metabolic alteration related to obesity [CITATION_1] , and it represents an important link between obesity and other metabolic as well as cardiovascular complications [CITATION_2] (Fig. 1) .",
